        "description": "Current Approach : \nStorageDescriptor class is used to describe parameters like InputFormat, Outputformat, SerDeInfo, etc. for a hive table.\nSome of the class variables like InputFormat, OutputFormat, SerDeInfo.serializationLib, etc. are required fields when\ncreating a storage descriptor object.\nFor example : createTable command in the metaStoreClient creates the table with the default values of such variables defined in HiveConf or hive-default.xml\nBut in unit tests, table is created in a slightly different way, that these values need to be set explicitly.\nThus, when creating tables in tests, required fieldes of StorageDescriptor object need to be set.\n\nIssue with current approach :\nFrom some of  the current usages of this class in unit tests, I noticed that\nwhen any one of the test cases tried to clean up the database and found a table created by any of the previously executed test cases,\nthe clean up process tries to fetch the Table object and performs the sanity checks which include checking for required fields like InputFormat, OutputFormat, SerDeInfo.serializationLib\nof the table. The sanity checks fail which results in failure of the test case.\n\nFix :\nIn unit-tests, StorageDescriptor object should be created with the Fields that are sanity checked when trying to fetch the table.\n\nNOTE : This fix fixes 6 test cases in itests/hive-unit/",
